          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">ASML faces a tough outlook amid reduced spending</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-jan-27-1.png" alt="ASML faces a tough outlook amid reduced spending" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">ASML’s next week’s earnings report will be keenly followed by analysts as the scrutiny around the company’s growth outlook continues to increase. ASML reported a weak result in the previous quarter, about <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-27-01-2025-h1-1-30-off-a-july-peak" target="_blank">30% off a July peak</a>, cutting its revenue guidance. The firm’s major clients, like Intel and Samsung, have cut down their capital expenditures due to their own issues. Moreover, Chinese customers are also now expected to reduce their buying, adding more to the worries of ASML.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
