              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Tesla unveils redesigned Model Y to boost sales</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;filter:blur(5px);">Tesla has launched a refreshed version of its best-selling car in the US, Canada, and Europe. The <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-27-01-2025-h2-2-new-model-y" target="_blank">new model Y</a>, available as a ‘Launch Series’ variant, is priced at $59,990 and would lease for $699 with $2,999 down. This is about 25% higher than the previous top models. Tesla’s self-driving system comes with the car, which is usually offered as an add-on for $8,000 in other vehicles. Its stock skidded in 2025 following a big fourth-quarter delivery miss and an overall down year for the electric vehicle maker.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
